{"cursor":"6076","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"'Background independence' is a condition in theoretical physics, especially in\nquantum gravity (QG), that requires the defining equations of a theory to be\nindependent of the actual shape of the spacetime and the value of various fields\nwithin the spacetime, and in particular to not refer to a specific coordinate\nsystem or metric. The different configurations (or backgrounds) should be\nobtained as different solutions of the underlying equations.\n","linknr":126,"url":"Background_independence","recorded":1362898491,"links":16,"instances":["mathematics","physics"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Theoretical physics","Philosophy of physics"],"headings":["Manifest background-independence","Theories of quantum gravity","See also","External links","References"],"image":["//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["field","physics"],["metric","mathematics"]],"members":["metric","field"],"related":["Theoretical_physics","Quantum_gravity","Spacetime","Field_(physics)","Coordinate_system","Metric_(mathematics)","Differentiable_manifold","General_relativity","Maxwell_equation","Minkowski_spacetime","Diffeomorphisms","Gauge_symmetry","Observable","String_theory","Perturbation_theory","String_field_theory","AdS/CFT","Anti-de_Sitter_space","Superselection","Loop_quantum_gravity","Topology","String_theory","General_relativity","String_theory","Causal_dynamical_triangulation","Loop_quantum_gravity","Quantum_field_theory","Coordinate-free","Lee_Smolin","Carlo_Rovelli","Edward_Witten","John_Stachel","Elie_Zahar"]}